The paper discusses the implementation of domain-specific languages (DSLs) and their compilation for execution on heterogeneous hardware. This topic falls under the programming languages (cs.PL), architecture (cs.AR), software engineering (cs.SE), distributed computing (cs.DC), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on building efficient DSL compilers, cs.PL is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant as they touch on various aspects of DSL implementation and optimization.
